	<entry xml:lang="en">
		<title type="html">Compiz on openSUSE 11.1</title>
		<link href="http://dev.compiz-fusion.org/~cyberorg/2008/12/04/compiz-on-opensuse-111/"/>
		<id>http://dev.compiz-fusion.org/~cyberorg/?p=181</id>
		<updated>2008-12-04T13:31:33+00:00</updated>
		<content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Although openSUSE 11.1 is almost ready, Compiz that is in it is still not there yet. If you run into some of the remaining annoyances, here is how to get Compiz Fusion bliss on openSUSE 11.1.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Add X11:XGL repository that contains compiz without &lt;a href=&quot;http://en.opensuse.org/Nomad&quot;&gt;NOMAD&lt;/a&gt; patches&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;zypper ar http://download.opensuse.org/repositories/X11:/XGL/openSUSE_11.1/ X11:XGL&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Update all compiz packages from that repo&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;zypper up -t package -r X11:XGL&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After making sure compiz is switched off and disabled, remove old configuration:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;rm -rf /home/your-username/.config/compiz&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Launch &lt;strong&gt;simple-ccsm&lt;/strong&gt; and enable Compiz.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have a lot of fun&amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
		<author>
			<name>Jigish Gohil</name>
			<uri>http://dev.compiz-fusion.org/~cyberorg</uri>
		</author>
