		<link href="http://dev.compiz-fusion.org/~cyberorg/2008/09/29/compiz-without-fglrx-on-opensuse-111/"/>
		<id>http://dev.compiz-fusion.org/~cyberorg/2008/09/29/compiz-without-fglrx-on-opensuse-111/</id>
		<updated>2008-09-29T17:45:50+00:00</updated>
		<content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Great news for the owners of on-board &lt;strong&gt;Radeon X1200/1250&lt;/strong&gt; Series graphics, &lt;strong&gt;fglrx is not required to run Compiz&lt;/strong&gt;. We can finally become completely &amp;#8220;free&amp;#8221;. We are using open source radeonhd drivers developed by SUSE engineers on the latest Xorg release.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Changed the following in xorg.conf and viola Compiz is running here!!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Section &amp;#8220;Device&amp;#8221;&lt;br /&gt;
Option &amp;#8220;DRI&amp;#8221; &amp;#8220;1&amp;#8243; #and this works even with radeonhd drivers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thanks to whoever is responsible for this &lt;img src=&quot;http://dev.compiz-fusion.org/~cyberorg/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif&quot; alt=&quot;:)&quot; class=&quot;wp-smiley&quot; /&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Update: Sndirsch just informs that this will be default on openSUSE 11.1, so probably rightÂ  from Beta 2 Compiz should work out of box on the hardwares using radeonhd drivers.&lt;/p&gt;</content>
