		<updated>2008-09-27T17:26:10+00:00</updated>
		<content type="html">Well, with the recent work by &lt;b&gt;pingouinfarceur&lt;/b&gt;, the Compiz Headtracking plugin is now alive and well!&lt;br /&gt;In my absence from the world of Compiz, pingouinfarceur took Wiitrack and integrated it with OpenCV to create webcam headtracking.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The end result is that headtracking is now a feasible, general-use plugin. I was honored to have my plugin expanded in such a way, and feel it is now my duty to make my end suck less.&lt;br /&gt;I've taken the time to change up the XML file for CCSM, moving things into separate tabs, reordering configuration options, changing labels, all to make the plugin better for active use.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;b&gt;Note&lt;/b&gt;: To compile &lt;i&gt;headtracking&lt;/i&gt;, you'll need to grab OpenCV from CVS (and it may not compile for you as is, I had troubles with their libtool script using $echo when it wasn't set).&lt;br /&gt;Well, enough of that, grab Headtracking and get going!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;font&gt;&lt;b&gt;Code:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font&gt;&lt;pre&gt;git clone git://anongit.compiz-fusion.org/users/klange/headtracking&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://ogunderground.com/article.php?id=38&quot;&gt;Discuss this news post here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;(No comments)</content>
