	<entry xml:lang="en">
		<title type="html">Compiz and Compiz Fusion 0.7.8 out</title>
		<link href="http://dev.compiz-fusion.org/~cyberorg/2008/09/23/compiz-and-compiz-fusion-078-out/"/>
		<id>http://dev.compiz-fusion.org/~cyberorg/2008/09/23/compiz-and-compiz-fusion-078-out/</id>
		<updated>2008-09-23T12:40:35+00:00</updated>
		<content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Danny Baumann &lt;a href=&quot;http://lists.freedesktop.org/archives/compiz/2008-September/003196.html&quot;&gt;announced&lt;/a&gt; the release of Compiz 0.7.8, Compiz Fusion project has followed up with a release of all Fusion components to match Compiz, here is the &lt;a href=&quot;http://lists.compiz-fusion.org/pipermail/dev/2008-September/001045.html&quot;&gt;announcement&lt;/a&gt; by Guillaume Seguin.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The release has many bug fixes, translation updates, a new plugin obs (opacity, brightness, saturation) and the reworked Animation plugin.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The good news for KDE users is: Lubos Lunak of Kwin4 fame is working on simple-ccsm-kde4, a GUI for managing compiz settings easily in KDE4 environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is still more exciting things to come in near future, a project codenamed &amp;#8220;NOMAD&amp;#8221;, watch out for more details as they emerge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The repository for openSUSE Compiz packages has moved from it&amp;#8217;s usual location &lt;a href=&quot;http://download.opensuse.org/repositories/X11:/XGL&quot;&gt;X11:XGL&lt;/a&gt; to new home &lt;a href=&quot;http://download.opensuse.org/repositories/X11:/Compiz/&quot;&gt;X11:Compiz &lt;/a&gt;so please adjust your repository settings accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The bug reports and enhancement requests welcome, &lt;a href=&quot;http://bugs.opencompositing.org/&quot;&gt;head to our bug tracker&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Edit: In case there is problem after update, please make sure you have packages from X11:Compiz repo and not the old one. Discable compiz. remove all old settingsÂ  (rm ~/.config/compiz*), and re-enable it from simple-ccsm.&lt;/p&gt;</content>
