	<entry xml:lang="en">
		<title type="html">RIP XGL</title>
		<link href="http://dev.compiz-fusion.org/~cyberorg/2008/07/26/rip-xgl/"/>
		<id>http://dev.compiz-fusion.org/~cyberorg/2008/07/26/rip-xgl/</id>
		<updated>2008-07-26T20:53:39+00:00</updated>
		<content type="html">&lt;p&gt;The X server technology that gave us &lt;a href=&quot;http://compiz-fusion.org&quot;&gt;Compiz&lt;/a&gt;, resulting possibly in inspiration of KDE4&amp;#8217;s kwin effects - &lt;a href=&quot;http://gitweb.freedesktop.org/?p=xorg/xserver.git;a=commit;h=d15b3790307053587df8daed1936ff6923881b63&quot;&gt;Xgl is no more&lt;/a&gt;. Xgl will also not be shipped on openSUSE 11.1 and SUSE Linux Enterprise 11.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://dev.compiz-fusion.org/~cyberorg/2008/07/26/rip-xgl/xgl/&quot; rel=&quot;attachment wp-att-136&quot; title=&quot;Xgl image by jimmac&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://dev.compiz-fusion.org/~cyberorg/files/2008/07/get-xgl.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Xgl image by jimmac&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So what would be in &lt;a href=&quot;http://en.opensuse.org/Roadmap&quot;&gt;openSUSE 11.1&lt;/a&gt; instead? &lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AIGLX&quot;&gt;AIGLX&lt;/a&gt; along with &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.x.org/wiki/DRI2&quot;&gt;DRI2&lt;/a&gt; will provide framework for the next generation of composite desktop effects. Nvidia drivers do not need either Xgl or AIGLX, now that &lt;a href=&quot;http://emmes.livejournal.com/&quot;&gt;Matthias Hopf&amp;#8217;s&lt;/a&gt; hand is almost fixed, hopefully we will have open source ATI radeonhd drivers with 3D capability in time for 11.0 &lt;img src=&quot;http://dev.compiz-fusion.org/~cyberorg/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif&quot; alt=&quot;:)&quot; class=&quot;wp-smiley&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
