	<entry xml:lang="en">
		<title type="html">Freewins fixes coming up</title>
		<link href="http://smspillaz.wordpress.com/2008/07/02/freewins-fixes-coming-up/"/>
		<id>http://smspillaz.wordpress.com/?p=283</id>
		<updated>2008-07-02T23:28:09+00:00</updated>
		<content type="html">&lt;div class=&quot;snap_preview&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;So some of you might have noticed that there is an interesting bug in freewins where if you rotate a window clockwise too much, the window will dissappear from screen. I know about this bug and I haven&amp;#8217;t really been able to fix it because I&amp;#8217;ve been trying something else recently, that is getting my laptop to quad boot MediaDirect, Vista, openSUSE, and Mac OS X. My efforts are finally finished now, so I am returning to development as soon as I can get compiz to build properly. (Small howto is in the read more section if you are interested)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anyways, the bug is caused by me replacing the disabling of backface culling with backface culling inversion so that freewins might work a bit better with plugins like group, cubeaddon and cube. My algorithm, however is a bit flawed as it takes the corners of the window and if the &amp;#8217;supposed&amp;#8217;Â top left hand corner is below the bottom left hand corner then the culling inverts. This doesn&amp;#8217;t exactly work right when it comes to 2D rotation, so I just need to adjust the algorithm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Also, if you haven&amp;#8217;t been watching the plugin development forum, you might want to take a look at the progress &lt;strong&gt;b0le&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://forum.compiz-fusion.org/showthread.php?p=62356#post62356&quot;&gt;has made with the input redirection X.org patches and freewins&lt;/a&gt;. I expect to be working with him as soon as I get the patches working myself.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;more-283&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Small &lt;strong&gt;howto quad boot your xps m1530&lt;/strong&gt; for those who are interested&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&amp;#8217;ll need:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;All the installation CD&amp;#8217;s the came with your xps m1530&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A live CD that comes with GParted and dd (I used ubuntu)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Linux distro of your choice install CD&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A patched OS X leopard CD (Make sure you bought leopard) and apple stickers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A spare HDD to do this on would help&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Backup everything on the laptop : we&amp;#8217;re gonna hose it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Throw in your MediaDirect CD and boot off it. Hit &amp;#8216;2&amp;#8242; and put in how big you want your vista partition to be&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hit &amp;#8216;y&amp;#8217; to blow everything away&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Eject the Media Direct CD&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install windows to the partition you created for it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install media direct in windows and test it all works&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Throw in your live CD and fire up GParted&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You should have 3 Partitions: DellUtility, Vista, Extended {Raw partition, MediaDirect}
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delete the huge partition under the extended partition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resize the extended partition so that you have AT LEAST 20GB of free space before it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create a raw partition in this free space before the extended partition (This will be for OS X)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create a big linux partition in the free space in the extended partition with ext3&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Also, create a /home and FAT32 share partition if you want&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create at least 4GB for swap if you want to hibernate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hit apply, your partition layout should look like this:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;DellUtility; Vista; Raw for OS X; Extended { ext3 for linux; ext3 /home;Â FAT32 share; linux_swap swap; FAT32 MediaDirect }&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reboot and check it all works (MediaDirect etc)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Now install your linux distro of choice to the big linux partition and set mount points accordingly. If you can, change the filesystem type of the raw partition to 0xAF&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make sure that when you install grub, you install it to the linux root partition, NOT the MBR&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Check it all works (You can&amp;#8217;t boot into linux yet)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Now throw in your Live CD and run this command:
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;sudo dd if=/dev/sda of=/home/username/mbr_bak.bin bs=512 count=1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Copy that file to a thumbdrive&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Download EasyBCD and add an entry for linux to the partition you installed grub on&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Throw in your OS X CD and install it as usuall, make sure darwin_boot is installed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;OS X should work, but you won&amp;#8217;t be able to boot anything else&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Boot into your live CD, get the MBR backup you made and run
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;sudo dd if=/home/username/mbr_bak.bin of=/dev/sda bs=512 count=1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Now your other OS&amp;#8217;s should work, but you can&amp;#8217;t boot into OS X&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Get a copy of the netkas pc_efi_v8 and copy &lt;strong&gt;boot_v8&lt;/strong&gt; to your /boot folder on you linux partition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Now, edit (as root) your /boot/grub/menu.lst and add an entry that looks like this
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;title Apple Mac OS X&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;kernel /boot/boot_v8&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You should be good to go. Save the file (make sure you back up the old one!) and select &amp;#8216;Mac OS X&amp;#8217; from your menu. It will ask you what disk number OS X is located on. Just enter &amp;#8216;80&amp;#8242; or leave it. From there, it should give you darwin_boot and you can boot OS X \o/. If you want the graphics drivers, just google for NVInject and continue with the default options. You&amp;#8217;ll have to force-power-off the system however when you shut it down after the screen goes blank because the drivers break these things.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In Vista, throw in your Dell Drivers CD and install all the drivers and re-run the Windows Experience Index test to get Aero.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have tons of fun (And don&amp;#8217;t forget to install Compiz-Fusion!)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Small Video of what you should get once you have everything install[ed:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://smspillaz.wordpress.com/2008/07/02/freewins-fixes-coming-up/&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://img.youtube.com/vi/4yqzPPT0KIw/2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; src=&quot;http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/categories/smspillaz.wordpress.com/283/&quot; /&gt; &lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; src=&quot;http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/tags/smspillaz.wordpress.com/283/&quot; /&gt; &lt;a rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; href=&quot;http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/smspillaz.wordpress.com/283/&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; src=&quot;http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/smspillaz.wordpress.com/283/&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; href=&quot;http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/smspillaz.wordpress.com/283/&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; src=&quot;http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/smspillaz.wordpress.com/283/&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; href=&quot;http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/smspillaz.wordpress.com/283/&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; src=&quot;http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/smspillaz.wordpress.com/283/&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; href=&quot;http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/smspillaz.wordpress.com/283/&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; src=&quot;http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/smspillaz.wordpress.com/283/&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; href=&quot;http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/smspillaz.wordpress.com/283/&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; src=&quot;http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/smspillaz.wordpress.com/283/&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; src=&quot;http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=smspillaz.wordpress.com&amp;amp;blog=1094742&amp;amp;post=283&amp;amp;subd=smspillaz&amp;amp;ref=&amp;amp;feed=1&quot; /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
		<author>
			<name>smspillaz</name>
			<uri>http://smspillaz.wordpress.com</uri>
