	<entry xml:lang="en">
		<title type="html">Getting NVIDIA and ATI drivers on openSUSE 11.0</title>
		<link href="http://dev.compiz-fusion.org/~cyberorg/2008/06/13/getting-nvidia-and-ati-drivers-on-opensuse-110/"/>
		<id>http://dev.compiz-fusion.org/~cyberorg/2008/06/13/getting-nvidia-and-ati-drivers-on-opensuse-110/</id>
		<updated>2008-06-13T14:41:36+00:00</updated>
		<content type="html">&lt;p&gt;openSUSE 11.0 just went Gold, and would be available on mirrors in 5 days, here is a handy guide to get ATI and NVIDIA drivers, use  whichever way that suite you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;Install ATI&quot; href=&quot;http://opensuse-community.org/ati.ymp&quot;&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;162&quot; height=&quot;46&quot; align=&quot;middle&quot; src=&quot;http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2232/1494964720_1c59cef7b0_o.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;Install NVIDIA&quot; href=&quot;http://opensuse-community.org/nvidia.ymp&quot;&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;160&quot; height=&quot;40&quot; align=&quot;middle&quot; src=&quot;http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2001/1494159137_929397bbb0_o.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Or commandline friendly&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;su -c &amp;#8220;OCICLI http://opensuse-community.org/ati.ymp&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;su -c &amp;#8220;OCICLI http://opensuse-community.org/nvidia.ymp&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One more commandline way via zypper:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NVIDIA:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;zypper sa http://download.nvidia.com/opensuse/11.0 nvidia&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;zypper in x11-video-nvidiaG01&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ATI:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;zypper sa http://www2.ati.com/suse/11.0 ati&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;zypper in Â x11-video-fglrxG01&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;No manual configuration of xorg.conf or switching on Xgl required to get compiz goodness, just launch simple-ccsm and enable compiz from there after installing the drivers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</content>
		<author>
			<name>Jigish Gohil</name>
			<uri>http://dev.compiz-fusion.org/~cyberorg</uri>
		</author>
